XIV. The same right has also been used towards hostages3 and not those only who have bound themselves by some sort of convention, but those who are delivered up by others. By the Thessalians there were put to death on one occasion two hundred and fifty: by the Romans, the Volsci Aurunci, to the number of three hundred.
